---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <div class="relative min-h-screen bg-black">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-24">
      <!-- Hero Section -->
      <div class="relative mb-32">
        <div class="bg-coral absolute top-0 -left-8 h-48 w-48"></div>
        <div class="bg-brand-orange-400 absolute top-1/2 -right-8 h-48 w-48">
        </div>
        <h1
          class="text-cream relative z-10 text-[12rem] leading-none font-black"
        >
          THE<br />
          STORY
        </h1>
        <div class="relative mt-8 flex items-center gap-8">
          <div class="bg-coral h-1 w-24"></div>
          <p class="text-cream text-xl font-bold">
            A journey through the making of something different
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- The Spark -->
      <div class="mb-32 grid gap-16 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="bg-brand-orange-400 absolute top-0 -left-8 h-32 w-32">
          </div>
          <div class="relative">
            <h2 class="text-cream mb-8 text-6xl font-black uppercase">
              The Spark
            </h2>
            <p class="text-cream text-xl leading-relaxed font-bold">
              In a world of increasingly complex web applications, we noticed
              something missing. The web had become bloated, over-designed, and
              often inaccessible. We wanted to create something different - a
              return to the raw, honest nature of the web.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="bg-coral absolute -right-8 bottom-0 h-32 w-32"></div>
          <div class="relative">
            <h2 class="text-cream mb-8 text-6xl font-black uppercase">
              The Vision
            </h2>
            <p class="text-cream text-xl leading-relaxed font-bold">
              We envisioned a website that would stand out not through flashy
              animations or trendy design, but through its brutal honesty and
              raw functionality. A place where content reigns supreme, and every
              element serves a purpose.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- The Journey -->
      <div class="mb-32">
        <div class="relative mb-16">
          <div class="bg-coral absolute top-0 -left-8 h-48 w-48"></div>
          <h2 class="text-cream relative text-8xl font-black uppercase">
            The Journey
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="grid gap-16 md:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="bg-brand-orange-400 absolute top-0 -left-4 h-4 w-4">
            </div>
            <div class="bg-coral absolute -right-4 bottom-0 h-4 w-4"></div>
            <div class="relative">
              <h3 class="text-cream mb-4 text-3xl font-black uppercase">
                The Build
              </h3>
              <p class="text-cream text-xl leading-relaxed font-bold">
                We chose Astro for its simplicity and performance. TypeScript
                for its clarity. Tailwind for its utility. Each tool was
                selected not for its popularity, but for its ability to help us
                achieve our vision.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="relative">
            <div class="bg-coral absolute top-0 -left-4 h-4 w-4"></div>
            <div class="bg-brand-orange-400 absolute -right-4 bottom-0 h-4 w-4">
            </div>
            <div class="relative">
              <h3 class="text-cream mb-4 text-3xl font-black uppercase">
                The Challenge
              </h3>
              <p class="text-cream text-xl leading-relaxed font-bold">
                Creating something simple is often the hardest task. We had to
                resist the temptation to add more features, more animations,
                more complexity. Every decision was questioned: "Does this serve
                our purpose?"
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="relative">
            <div class="bg-brand-orange-400 absolute top-0 -left-4 h-4 w-4">
            </div>
            <div class="bg-coral absolute -right-4 bottom-0 h-4 w-4"></div>
            <div class="relative">
              <h3 class="text-cream mb-4 text-3xl font-black uppercase">
                The Result
              </h3>
              <p class="text-cream text-xl leading-relaxed font-bold">
                What emerged was more than a website - it was a statement. A
                declaration that the web doesn't need to be complicated to be
                effective. That sometimes, the most powerful design is the one
                that gets out of the way.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- The Future -->
      <div class="relative">
        <div class="bg-brand-orange-400 absolute top-0 -right-8 h-48 w-48">
        </div>
        <div class="relative">
          <h2 class="text-cream mb-8 text-6xl font-black uppercase">
            The Future
          </h2>
          <p class="text-cream text-xl leading-relaxed font-bold">
            This is just the beginning. We're committed to maintaining this
            approach as we grow. Every new feature, every update, will be held
            to the same standard: does it serve our purpose? Does it maintain
            our commitment to honesty and simplicity?
          </p>
          <p class="text-cream mt-8 text-xl leading-relaxed font-bold">
            Join us on this journey. Help us prove that the web doesn't need to
            be complicated to be powerful.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
